                            <comment id="14959118" author="nsuke" created="Thu, 15 Oct 2015 15:58:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems to me too inconsistent with the existing stack.&lt;br/&gt;
Making every read/write call virtual is something the rest of C++ stack specifically avoid.&lt;br/&gt;
I think the reasonable way to implement this feature is to follow what TTransport and TProtocol do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14959125" author="hcorg" created="Thu, 15 Oct 2015 16:00:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TTransport and TProtocol does it when objects are generated with template support, TBase class will not be added when generating in &quot;template&quot; mode.&lt;br/&gt;
As much as I do not like general TBase class, I think it should not add a lot to existing stack&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
